To find out how long it takes to slide down the longest water slide (the one measuring 300ft), we need to divide its length by their speed:  
Time taken to travel distance = Distance traveled divided by Speed of movement  
For this case: Time_taken=Distance / Speed; hence Time_for_biggest_slide=(300 ft) /(60 ft/min)=5 min ;

First let us calculate time taken for both slides separately using formula Time=Distance / Speed;
For largest slide : Time_Largest = Distance(Largest Slide)/Speed (at Largest) =>  
Time_Largest = 300ft / 60ft/min = 5 minutes ;

Similarly, we can find out time required for smaller slide as well;   
=> Time_Smaller = 240 ft / 80ft per minute = 3 Minutes .
Now, To get difference , We just need to subtract these values i.e.,    
Difference = Larger Value – Smaller value ==> Difference = Time_largest – Time_smaller ====     
                       = 5 mins – 3 mints ====        
	        = 2 Mins Hence It takes extra two minutes than Small Waterslides !!!
